<subSubSection id="C305EAC0691EFFC3FC98FA47670DF918" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B691EFFC3FC98FA47670DF918" blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FC98FA47673EFA39" bold="true" box="[199,308,1477,1503]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA691EFFC3FECBFA46653DFA39" author="Calvert, P. P." box="[660,823,1476,1503]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="73 - 280" refId="ref11549" refString="Calvert, P. P. (1909) Contributions to a knowledge of the Odonata of the Neotropical region, exclusive of Mexico and Central America. Annals of the Carnegie Museum, 6 (3), 73 - 280." type="journal article" year="1909">Calvert (1909)</bibRefCitation>
based on a male collected in Coroico (
<collectingCountry id="F308F9DB691EFFC3F8BCFA466331FA39" box="[1251,1339,1476,1503]" name="Bolivia" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
), including an illustration of cerci in dorsolateral view. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA691EFFC3FEFAFA6A655AF9E5" author="Sjostedt, Y." box="[677,848,1512,1539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref12124" refString="Sjostedt, Y. (1918) Wissenschaftliche Ergbnisse der Swedischen Entomologischen Reise des Herrn Dr. A. Roman in Amazonas 1914 - 1915. 1, Odonata. Arkiv vor Zoologi, 11 (15), 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1918">Sjöstedt (1918)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C8691EFFC3FF97FA6B6255F9E4" box="[968,1119,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FF97FA6B6255F9E4" box="[968,1119,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single male from 
<collectingCountry id="F308F9DB691EFFC3FCC8F98F66C0F9C1" box="[151,202,1549,1575]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Peru</collectingCountry>
and illustrated cerci in dorsolateral view, as well as color pattern of abdomen in dorsal view. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA691EFFC3F895F98E6396F9C1" author="Williamson, E. B." box="[1226,1436,1548,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref12284" refString="Williamson, E. B. (1919) Results of the University of Michigan - Williamson expedition to Colombia, 1916 - 17. IV. Notes on species of the genus Heteragrion Selys with descriptions of new species (Odonata). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan, 68, 1 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14454" type="journal article" year="1919">Williamson (1919)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated color pattern of head and posterior lobe of prothorax of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C8691EFFC3FF2CF9B3630BF9AD" authority=", De Marmels (1987)" authorityName=", De Marmels" authorityYear="1987" box="[883,1281,1584,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidorsum">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FF2CF9B36210F9AD" box="[883,1050,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. flavidorsum</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA691EFFC3F878F9B3630BF9AD" author="De Marmels, J." box="[1063,1281,1584,1611]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" pagination="225 - 238" refId="ref11626" refString="De Marmels, J. (1987) On the type specimens of some neotropical Megapodagrionidae, with a description of Heteragrion pemon spec. nov. and Oxystigma caerulans spec. nov. from Venezuela (Zygoptera). Odonatologica, 16 (3), 225 - 238." type="journal article" year="1987">De Marmels (1987)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
examined the 
<typeStatus id="54A407E9691EFFC3FCC8F9D666F3F988" box="[151,249,1620,1646]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C8691EFFC3FD40F9D767BCF988" box="[287,438,1621,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FD40F9D767BCF988" box="[287,438,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and illustrated cerci and coloration pattern of head and thorax, arriving at the conclusion that 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C8691EFFC3FC98F9FB6757F974" box="[199,349,1657,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FC98F9FB6757F974" box="[199,349,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C8691EFFC3FE3EF9FB6502F975" authorityName=", De Marmels" authorityYear="1987" box="[609,776,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidorsum">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FE3EF9FB6502F975" box="[609,776,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">H. flavidorsum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Here, we report this species for 
<collectingCountry id="F308F9DB691EFFC3F82CF9FA62EEF974" box="[1139,1252,1656,1682]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, from 
<collectingRegion id="49DB77A9691EFFC3F974F9FB6715F951" country="Colombia" name="Putumayo" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Putumayo Department</collectingRegion>
. Some important diagnostic characters of this species are the male cerci lacking a ventrobasal convexity (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE691EFFC3FC99F942672AF93D" box="[198,288,1728,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 9H</figureCitation>
) and provided with a very short middle process (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE691EFFC3FF0AF9426593F93D" box="[853,921,1728,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[353,1234,776,1843]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male cerci: H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415717/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
G–H). The females of this species was so far unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C305EAC0691EFFDCFC98F88A64F9F865" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="106" pageId="15" pageNumber="105" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B691EFFC3FC98F88A6559F88D" blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FC98F88A67F2F8C5" bold="true" box="[199,504,1800,1827]" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Description of the female</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FE56F88B644CF8C5" box="[521,582,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Head</emphasis>
: mainly brown, labrum dark brown with orange central spot, clypeus dark brown, black crossbar at level of antenna, antennal base dark brown, brown crossbar at level of ocelli and a black crossbar along posterior margin, rear of head brown (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE691EFFC3FEB3F8D2654CF88D" box="[748,838,1872,1899]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[359,1216,453,1446]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[359,1227,453,1446]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Face color pattern: H. calendulum (taken from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez 2017): (A) male Pueblo Rico, Risaralda (B) female Pueblo Rico, Risaralda. Heteragrion demarmelsi: (C) male Leticia, Amazonas (D) female Leticia, Amazo- nas. Heteragrion erythrogastrum: (E) male Union Panamericana, Chocó (F) female Union Panamericana, Chocó. Heteragrion flavidorsum: (G) male PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (H) female PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo. H. inca: (I) male Puerto Legui- zamo, Putumayo (J) female Puerto Leguizamo, Putumayo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415709/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 5H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B691EFFDCFC98F8F764B6FE6D" blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,153,395]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="106" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FC98F8F76733F869" box="[199,313,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Prothorax</emphasis>
: anterior lobe black with gray central spot, middle lobe dark gray with two black dorsal spots, posterior lobe black with pale brown posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE691EFFC3FEE3F81A6529F855" box="[700,803,1944,1971]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 16K</figureCitation>
), dorsal plate of intersternite with swollen anterior corner (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE691EFFC3FCFFF83E6709F831" box="[160,259,1980,2007]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Fig. 14F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B96B6559691EFFC3FD48F83F6797F831" box="[279,413,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="105">Pterothorax</emphasis>
: mesepisternum pale brown with black middorsal line and black antehumeral stripe, mesepimeron gray with black stripe, mesinfraespisternum gray with black spot, metepisternum pale brown with black stripe, metepimeron pale yellow, metinfraepisternum pale yellow with black spot (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6901FFDCF814FF1B62BCFF52" box="[1099,1206,153,180]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Fig. 16G</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCF893FF18630BFF55" box="[1228,1281,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Legs</emphasis>
: dark brown, spurs on femora about same size as space between them, except for distal three, which are longer on profemora, and the distal four longer on mesofemora; there are seven spurs on profemora, eight on mesofemora and 11 on metafemora; spurs on tibiae about two times as long as space between them, except for distal three which are shorter on protibiae and metatibiae; there are ten spurs on protibiae, seven on mesotibiae and 11 on metatibiae, tarsi and claw dark brown. 
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFD7AFECC6763FE81" box="[293,361,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Wings</emphasis>
: hyaline, with brown veins and pale brown pterostigma, which covers 2.5 cells, and has slanting proximal and distal edges, 17 Px in FW and HW.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF60E9C36901FFDCFCC8FA5C649AF985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253606/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="106" startId="16.[151,250,1502,1527]" targetBox="[386,1205,422,1464]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B6901FFDCFCC8FA5C649AF985" blockId="16.[151,1436,1502,1635]" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFCC8FA5C6728FA11" bold="true" box="[151,290,1502,1527]" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">FIGURE 15.</emphasis>
Female structures: 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86901FFDCFDAFFA5D6506FA11" authority=": Puerto Leguizamo" authorityName="Puerto Leguizamo" box="[496,780,1502,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFDAFFA5D6437FA10" box="[496,573,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">H. inca</emphasis>
: Puerto Leguizamo
</taxonomicName>
, Putumayo (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. 
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFD43F9816410F9FC" box="[284,538,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFD43F98167B2F9FC" box="[284,440,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86901FFDCFD43F9816793F9FC" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[284,409,1539,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteragrion</taxonomicName>
m.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86901FFDCFDE2F98164BBF9FD" authority=": Puerto Berrio" authorityName="Puerto Berrio" box="[445,689,1538,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mitratum">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFDE2F9816410F9FC" box="[445,538,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">mitratum</emphasis>
: Puerto Berrio
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, Antioquia (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite (modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA6901FFDCFD65F9A464CDF9D8" author="Bota-Sierra, C. A. &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, R." box="[314,711,1574,1599]" pageId="16" pageNumber="106" pagination="553 - 571" refId="ref11240" refString="Bota-Sierra, C. A. &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, R. (2017) The genus Heteragrion (Odonata: Zygoptera) in Northwestern Colombia, with the description of Heteragrion tatama sp. nov. Zootaxa, 4347 (3), 553 - 571. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4347.3.8" type="journal article" year="2017">Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86901FFDCFE87F9A562BCF9D9" authority=": Union Panamericana" authorityName="Union Panamericana" box="[728,1206,1574,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="16" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinum">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFE87F9A565DBF9D8" box="[728,977,1575,1598]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Heteragrion peregrinum</emphasis>
: Union Panamericana
</taxonomicName>
, Chocó (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B6901FFDCFC98F9136217F8F1" blockId="16.[151,1437,1681,1923]" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFC98F913673BF94D" box="[199,305,1681,1707]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Abdomen</emphasis>
: mainly brown, S1–S2 paler laterally, S3–S7 with pale brown basal ring, S3–S6 with pale brown lateroventral spot in distal half, S9–S10 brown dorsally and pale brown ventrally (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6901FFDCF84AF9376274F936" box="[1045,1150,1717,1744]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1180,1205]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[349,1237,181,1161]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 16. Female structures: H. tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (D) male habitus (E) female habitus. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (F) female habitus. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (G) female habitus. Heteragrion demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (H) male thorax dorsal (I) female thorax dorsal. Heteragrion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (J) female throax dorsal. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (K) female thorax dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253608/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Fig. 16G</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCF8CEF9376303F929" box="[1169,1289,1717,1743]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Ovipositor</emphasis>
: pale brown, not surpassing end of S10, stylus pale brown (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6901FFDCFEFEF95B6503F915" box="[673,777,1753,1779]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
), small dark brown teeth on genital valves in a parallel arrangement (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6901FFDCFD42F97F6766F8F1" box="[285,364,1789,1815]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
D–E), cerci dark brown basally and black distally (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6901FFDCFFF7F97F621AF8F1" box="[936,1040,1789,1815]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1334,1359]" captionTargetBox="[378,1207,314,1306]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[370,1218,309,1314]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Female structures: H. erythrogastrum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion flavidorsum: PNN Churumbelos, Putumayo (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite. H. demarmelsi: Leticia, Amazonas (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253604/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B6901FFDCFC98F8A06557F8DD" blockId="16.[151,1437,1681,1923]" box="[199,861,1825,1851]" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFC98F8A06763F8DD" box="[199,361,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Measurements</emphasis>
(mm): Abdomen: 36.0, FW: 29.0, HW:28.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B6901FFDCFC98F8C664F9F865" blockId="16.[151,1437,1681,1923]" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="B96B65596901FFDCFC98F8C66479F8B9" bold="true" box="[199,627,1860,1887]" pageId="16" pageNumber="106">Variation among examined females</emphasis>
: similar coloration, 17–18 Px in FW and 16–17 Px in HW. Abdomen 36.0–37.0mm, FW 25.0–26.0mm, HW 25.0–26.0mm.
</paragraph>
